Police in KwaZulu-Natal say they have arrested a man who allegedly shot and killed African National Congress Youth League PEC member, Sindisiwe Ndlovu in the Thokoza area of Crammond in the midlands. Ndlovu aged 34 had served in various committees of the ANC Youth League. KwaZulu-Natal police Spokesperson, Thembeka Mbhele says the suspect and Ndlovu had an argument and he shot her in the chest. Mbhele says the suspect will be appearing in court soon. She says, “34-year-old woman was shot and killed by an alleged boyfriend in the Thokozani area after an argument. The incident took place this morning (Tuesday) round about 2 o’clock and the suspect was placed under arrest. The 31-year-old suspect he will be appearing in court soon.”